The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in clinical health care applications, which involves machine learning and computer vision techniques (cs.LG, cs.CV). The authors also emphasize the importance of relevant clinical questions and the need for high-quality data, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of developing AI algorithms for biomedical applications, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the authors highlight the importance of regulatory compliance and validation, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
